A recent court case in which a pay television service sued local internet providers for failure to take down links that illegally streamed the company’s licensed sports content highlights the challenge piracy poses to content producers.
The distribution of unlicensed content may hinder the development of the television industry in Africa. In the last decade, the rise in digital television stations in Kenya has offered viewers a variety of local and international content.



