An increasing demand in content and competition for audiences has forced digital content providers to seek innovative ways to fill their broadcast schedules.
One of the requirements for a commercial free-to-air television licence as laid down by the Communications Authority of Kenya (CAK) is to submit a plan that includes the particulars of the proposed station’s programming schedule.



