This includes strategies pertaining to self-produced programmes and their weekly proportions and any planned external source of programming.
Another key requirement is a quality assurance plan. Both of these are meant to ensure that licence holders have developed solid strategic content development plans.
Unauthorised content
However, the challenge of producing local quality programmes has led some providers to take advantage of weak enforcement to distribute unauthorised content either by the direct download of YouTube material and then re-broadcasting on their channels, or playing unlicensed movies.
Unlicensed and pirated content often exhibit poor quality video and audio [and] may present in a foreign language without subtitles.
Fast internet access, lack of adequate legislation, increased participation of organised cross-border pirates and more recently, an upsurge in audience due to Covid-19 containment measures means that video piracy is on the rise.



