According to global tech advisory firm AB Research, more than 17 per cent of worldwide video streaming users are consuming content illegally.
Tackling the piracy menace should include improved monitoring and self-regulation. Section 8 of CAK’s Programming Code for Broadcasting Services 2019 states that broadcasters must have contracts with copyright licensing bodies or authorised legal vendors before running copyrighted material and “shall, upon request, submit such contracts to the authority”. Innovation in the local broadcast industry is inevitable.
